data.title: Lil Dickey "Life Lessons Tour"
data.meta_description: Rapper and comedian Lil Dickey will bring his “Life Lessons Tour” to the St. Augustine Amphitheatre with special guests Mustard and Oliver Tree.
data.text:
The St. Augustine Amphitheatre presents rapper, comedian, and underwear model Lil Dickey on his "Life Lessons Tour" with special guests Mustard and Oliver Tree on Monday, October 29, 2018. This will be Lil Dickey's only stop in Florida on this tour.

AKA Dave Burd, Lil Dickey first achieved acclaimed and commercial success with his album Professional Rapper. That album debuted at #7 on the Billboard Hot 100 and #1 on the Comedy, Rap, and Independent Charts. Lil Dickey's most recent single, "Freaky Friday," has surpassed over 600 million global streams in just a few months.

A Los Angeles native who was born Dijon McFarlane, DJ Mustard is an award-winning artist and producer. He has sold over 20 million singles in just three years, along with collaborating with Fergie, Jennifer Lopes, Wiz Khalifa, Trey Songz, and more. Mustard was named the No. 1 Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs Producers of 2014 by Billboard, and in 2015 he became the first artist to win both R&B/Hip-Hop Songwriter of the Year and R&B/Hip-Hop producer of the Year at the BMI R&B/Hip-Hop Awards.

Oliver Tree is known for his high-energy sound and his eccentric persona on stage. He released the critically acclaimed debut EP Alien Boy, which debuted at #5 on iTunes. Primarily a pianist, guitarist, and producer, Tree is also adept at incorporating rap, male and female vocal harmonies, lyrics, strings, and synth into his productions.

For more information about Lil Dickey, DJ Mustard, and Oliver Tree, and for details about this concert, please visit here.

Admission: Tickets at $49.50 for General Admission Pit, $45.00 for Level 100, $39.50 for Level 200 and Level 300, and $29.50 for Obstructed View. See seating chart below.

When: Monday, October 29, 2018, at 6:30 p.m. Gates open at 5:00 p.m.

Where: St. Augustine Amphitheatre is located at 1340 A1A South in St. Augustine, FL 32080.

Parking Information: The St. Augustine Amphitheatre is located on Anastasia Island next to Anastasia State Park. Limited paid parking is available in the St. Augustine Amphitheatre Main Lot, but only with advance purchase of a Premium Parking ticket. Free satellite parking areas are located within one mile of the Amphitheatre, at R.B. Hunt Elementary and at Anastasia State Park (see map below).

Shuttle Information: The St. Augustine Amphitheatre shuttle system begins its run 45 minutes prior to show time. The shuttle will pick up event patrons at four designated shuttle stops: the R.B. Hunt Elementary School Soccer Field, the west entrance of the Anastasia State Park Main Parking Lot, the Loop at the Anastasia State Park, and the entrance of the St. Augustine Amphitheatre. To see the full shuttle route, please see the map below.

Shuttles will run continuously until approximately 45 minutes after the scheduled start time of a concert. For anyone wanting to leave prior to the end of a show, shuttles will begin taking people back to the satellite parking areas one hour before the event is over. The driver will not depart the Amphitheatre until the shuttle is more than 50% full.
